elude.html#PUnit\">PUnit.{u_1 + 1}</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/SetTheory/Surreal/Dyadic.html#SetTheory.PGame.powHalf_leftMoves","kind":"theorem","line":58,"name":"SetTheory.PGame.powHalf_leftMoves","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/SetTheory/Surreal/Dyadic.lean#L58-L58"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/SetTheory/Surreal/Dyadic.html#SetTheory.PGame.powHalf_zero\"><span class=\"name\">SetTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">PGame</span>.<span class=\"name\">powHalf_zero</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/SetTheory/Surreal/Dyadic.html#SetTheory.PGame.powHalf\">powHalf</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/SetTheory/Surreal/Dyadic.html#SetTheory.PGame.powHalf_zero","kind":"theorem","line":54,"name":"SetTheory.PGame.powHalf_zero","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/SetTheory/Surreal/Dyadic.lean#L54-L56"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/SetTheory/Surreal/Dyadic.html#SetTheory.PGame.powHalf\"><span class=\"name\">SetTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">PGame</span>.<span class=\"name\">powHalf</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/SetTheory/PGame/Basic.html#SetTheory.PGame\">PGame</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For a natural number `n`, the pre-game `powHalf (n + 1)` is recursively defined as\n`{0 | powHalf n}`. These are the explicit expressions of powers of `1 / 2`. By definition, we have\n`powHalf 0 = 1` and `powHalf 1 ≈ 1 / 2` and we prove later on that\n`powHalf (n + 1) + powHalf (n + 1) ≈ powHalf n`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/SetTheory/Surreal/Dyadic.html#SetTheory.PGame.powHalf","kind":"def","line":46,"name":"SetTheory.PGame.powHalf","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/SetTheory/Surreal/Dyadic.lean#L46-L52"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Algebra.Algebra.Defs","Mathlib.Algebra.Order.Group.Basic","Mathlib.GroupTheory.MonoidLocalization.Away","Mathlib.RingTheory.Localization.Defs","Mathlib.SetTheory.Game.Birthday","Mathlib.SetTheory.Surreal.Multiplication","Mathlib.Tactic.Linarith","Mathlib.Tactic.Linter.DeprecatedModule"],"instances":[{"className":"Unique","name":"SetTheory.PGame.uniquePowHalfLeftMoves","typeNames":["SetTheory.PGame.LeftMoves"]},{"className":"IsEmpty","name":"SetTheory.PGame.isEmpty_powHalf_zero_rightMoves","typeNames":["SetTheory.PGame.RightMoves"]},{"className":"Unique","name":"SetTheory.PGame.uniquePowHalfSuccRightMoves","typeNames":["SetTheory.PGame.RightMoves"]}],"name":"Mathlib.SetTheory.Surreal.Dyadic"}